<div style="width: 740px; border: 1px dashed gray; padding: 10px;  margin:0px auto;">
<h2>Appointment SetUp</h2><hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
<div class="clear"></div>
This screen captures the Patient Appointments setup information for the department. This screen is used for maintaining appointments setup based on department available days. This screen will contain information of Week Days, No of doctors, From time, To time, Slot Duration, Break Time, Max no of days, Min no of days, Before time. This screen can use one time setup only.
<br /><hr /><br />
<img src="images/app_appointmentsetup.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />
<p>
<span class="title">Department:</span><br />
    User can select the departmentlist from the given list, this will come from department screen, it will display only OPD departnments, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">No. of Doctors: </span> <br />
 No of doctors available in the department, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">From Time: </span> 
    <br />OPD starting time, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">To Time: </span> 
    <br />	OPD closing time, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Slot Duration: </span> 
    <br />	Slot duration of each Patient, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Break From Time:</span> 
    <br />	Break from time between from time and to time, it can remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Break To Time:</span> 
    <br />	Break to (Closing) time between from time and to time, it can remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Max No. of days:</span> 
    <br />	User can enter maximum number of days for giving OPD appointments, it can remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Min No. of days:</span> 
    <br />	User can enter minimum number of days for giving OPD appointments, it can remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Submit (Button):</span> 
    <br />	By clicking on Save button user can save the data. 
    <br />
    <span class="title">Reset (Button):</span> 
    <br />	Clicking on reset button, will clear the current or existing data.


</p>




</div>
